(1)
East River Drive, north from East 93rd to and including East 95th Streets. Prominent building shown on East 95th Street at the East River, is an electric generating plant of the Consolidated Gas Co.
September 23, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, slightly later.
March 7, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
A closer view of the power house as seen from the dock at East 94th Street.
March 7, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

(1)
East River Drive, north from East 93rd Street (before its completion) and showing coal barges tied up at the foot of East 96th Street, in the East River. At the left appears a New York Edison Company building, extending from East 95th to East 96th Streets.
March 29, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, northward from East 94th Street. In the center background appears a view of the rear of Public School No. 99, fronting on the south side of East 100th Street, between the East River Drive and First Ave.

March 29, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
